# Development

## Requirements
Node.js + Yarn/npm


## Run the web client
`cd web/` then
`npm run serve`

## Run the server
`cd server` then
`npm run serve`

## Open browser
Open <http://localhost:8080/> and check if things are working


## Docker

### Step 1
cd web/ 

### Step 2 - set the TARGET_DIRECTORY  to your universe path
TARGET_DIRECTORY=/home/other-user/documents/zettelkasten docker-compose up
TARGET_DIRECTORY=/home/user-example/universe-path docker-compose up
TARGET_DIRECTORY=/home/ubuntu/z docker-compose up

### Step 3 - In ilse config set target-directory to /app
This is so that we'll map docker's volume to your dir and then from the volume to the server

